array/toObj.description: Transform an array into an object, where keys are indices, and values are elements.

array/toObjBy.description: Given a function that generates a key, turns a list of objects into an object indexing the objects by the given key

array/shuffle.description:
Immutably randomize array element order
Fisher-Yates shuffle

async/race.description:
Returns a promise that resolves or rejects as soon as one of the promises in an
iterable resolves or rejects, with the value or reason from that promise.

async/deferWith.description: Defers invoking a function until the current call stack has cleared. Passes args to deferred function.

async/defer.description: Defers invoking a function until the current call stack has cleared

async/toAsync.description: Wraps a function to always return a promise

async/fromCallback.description: Returns a promise that is resolved by an err-back function
examples:
await fromCallback(cb => cb(null, 123)); // 123
await fromCallback(cb => cb(Error('oops'))); // Error('oops')

async/retryWith.description: Wrap a function to retry based on a predicate function

async/promisify.description: Make an errback-calling function promise-returning. Inverse of callbackify
examples:
const callback = (n, cb) => cb(null, n + 1);
await promisify(callback)(1); // 2

async/callbackify.description: Make a promise-returning function errback-yielding. Inverse of promisify

async/pipe.description: serial + async R.pipe. works with sync or async functions

async/flatMapPairsLimit.sig: Number → ([a, b] → Promise<[[c, d]]>) → { a: b } → Promise<{ c: d }>
async/flatMapPairsLimit.description: Flat map pairs with variable parallelization

async/mapPairsLimit.sig: Number → ([a, b] → Promise<[c, d]>) → { a: b } → Promise<{ c: d }>
examples:
// { 1: 'a', 2: 'b', 3: 'c' }
await mapPairsLimit(2, async pair => pair.reverse(), { a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 });

async/flatMapPairs.sig: ([a, b] → Promise<[[c, d]]>) → { a: b } → Promise<{ c: d }>

async/flatMapPairsSeries.sig: ([a, b] → Promise<[[c, d]]>) → { a: b } → Promise<{ c: d }>

async/mapPairs.sig: ([a, b] → Promise<[c, d]>) → { a: b } → Promise<{ c: d }>
examples:
// { 1: 'a', 2: 'b', 3: 'c' }
await mapPairs(async pair => pair.reverse(), { a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 });

async/mapPairsSeries.sig: ([a, b] → Promise<[c, d]>) → { a: b } → Promise<{ c: d }>
examples:
// { 1: 'a', 2: 'b', 3: 'c' }
await mapPairsSeries(async pair => pair.reverse(), { a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 });

async/evolve.sig: { k: (a → Promise<b>) } → { k: a } → Promise<{ k: b }>

color/rgbToHsl.sig: { r, g, b } → { h, s, l }

color/hslToRgb.sig: { h, s, l } → { r, g, b }

color/rgbToHex.todo:: should this not include the hash prefix?

datetime/now.description: Get the current unix epoch (in ms)

function/on.sig: (b → b → c) → (a → b) → a → a → c

function/once.description:
Creates a function that is restricted to invoking func once.
Repeat calls to the function return the value of the first invocation

http/parseContentType.description: Parse a content-type HTTP header into its parts

examples:
isObject({}); // true
isObject([]]); // false
isObject(null); // false

iterable/async/map.description: Applies a function to each of an async iterable's yielded items. Works on all iterables

iterable/async/from.description: Returns an async iterator from an iterable

iterable/async/nextOr.description: Return the first or "next" item with a default value if iterable is empty
examples:
await nextOr(10, from([1, 2, 3])); // 1
await nextOr(10, from([])); // 10

iterable/async/next.description: Returns the first or "next" item. aka head

iterable/async/flatMap.description: Maps a function over an iterable and concatenates the results. a.k.a. "chain"

iterable/async/of.description: Create an iterator of one or more (variadic) arguments

examples:
// 6
await reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0, from([1, 2, 3]));

iterable/async/zipAllWith.description: Zip multiple iterators with custom zipping function

iterable/async/zipAll.description:
Zip an array of iterables into an iterables of arrays of items from corresponding indices
of the input iterables

iterable/async/zipWith.description: Zip two iterables with a custom zipping function

iterable/async/zip.description:
Zips two iterables into pairs of items from corresponding indices
of the input iterables. truncated to shorter of two iterables

iterable/async/rangeStep.description: Iterates from 0 to n by with a step (exclusive)

iterable/async/enumerate.description: Transform an iterable to an iterable of pairs of indices and their items

iterable/async/slice.description: Slice an async iterator between two indices

iterable/async/concat.description: Yield all items from one iterator, then the other

iterable/async/prepend.description: Prepend an item `a` to the end of an iterable

iterable/async/append.description: Append an item `a` to the start of an iterable

iterable/async/forEach.description: Run a function (side-effect) once for each item

iterable/async/filter.description: Yield only items that pass the predicate

iterable/async/reject.description: Yield only items that do not pass the predicate

iterable/async/flattenN.description: Flattens n-levels of a nested iterable of iterables

iterable/async/unnest.description: Flattens one level of a nested iterable of iterables

iterable/async/flatten.description: Flattens a nested iterable of iterables into a single iterable

iterable/async/iterate.description: Iterate infinitely, yielding items from seed through a predicate

iterable/async/some.description: Does any item pass the predicate?

iterable/async/none.description: Do all items fail the predicate?

iterable/async/uniqueWith.description: Yield only items that are unique by the predicate

iterable/async/unique.description: Yield only the unique items in an iterable (by strict equality)

iterable/async/take.description: Yield only the first n items of an iterable

iterable/async/drop.description: Drop the first n items of an iterable

iterable/async/tail.description: Yield all but the first item

iterable/async/times.description: Yield an item (a) n times. aka replicate

iterable/async/count.description: Return the number of items in an iterable. exhasts input

iterable/async/toArray.description: Transforms an async iterable to an array. exhasts input

iterable/async/nth.description: Returns the element at the nth index

iterable/async/every.description: Do all items pass their predicate?

iterable/async/reverse.todo:: there might be a more efficient strategy for arrays. generators are not iterable in reverse

iterable/async/frame.description: Yield a sliding "window" of length n. note: caches n items

iterable/async/dropLast.description: Yield all but the last n items. note: caches n + 1 items

iterable/async/init.description: Yield all but the last 1 item

iterable/async/tee.description: Copy an iterator n times (exhausts its input)

iterable/async/splitAt.description: Split an async iterable into a pair of iterables at a particular index

iterable/async/partition.description: Split an aynsc iterable into a pair of iterables based on the truthiness of their predicate

iterable/async/cycleN.description: Yield all items from an iterator, n times

iterable/async/cycle.description: Yield iterable items cyclically, infinitely looping when exhausted

iterable/async/unzipN.description: Transforms an iterable of n-tuple into an n-tuple of iterables

iterable/async/unzip.description: Transforms an iterable of pairs into a pairs of iterables

iterable/async/intersperse.description: Insert an item `a` between every item in the iterable

iterable/async/joinWith.description: Serialize iterator items to a string with an arbitrary spacer

iterable/async/join.description: Serialize iterator items to a string

iterable/async/isEmpty.description: Is an iterable empty? (done or length = 0)
examples:
await isEmpty(from([])); // true
await isEmpty(from([1])); // false

iterable/async/indices.description: Get an iterator of indices (0 to length - 1)

iterable/async/padTo.description: Pad an iterable with with a finite number of items `a`

iterable/async/pad.description: Pad iterable with an infinite number of items `a`
